# Three.js Performance Guardrails

- For MVP-1, keep scene minimal: basic lighting, simple geometry, lightweight assets.
- Avoid unnecessary per-frame allocations in render/update loops.
- Keep animation/update logic centralized and measurable.
- Defer visual polish that harms stability or FPS.
- Prefer interaction clarity over visual complexity.
- Introduce optimization only when a concrete bottleneck is observed.
